"38:8:14" : {s: 38, a: 8, w: 14, r: "ذوق", t: "يَذُوقُوا۟", l: "ذَاقُ", lc: 36, tl: "yadhūqū", lb: "আস্বাদন করা, স্বাদ গ্রহণ করা",e: "they have tasted", b: "তারা আস্বাদন করে", i: "mereka merasakan", f: 1, rm: "to taste/experience/try/perceive. One who tastes, cause to taste."},
"38:8:15" : {s: 38, a: 8, w: 15, r: "عذب", t: "عَذَابِ", l: "عَذَاب", lc: 322, tl: "ʿadhābi", lb: "শাস্তি, আযাব, দুর্যোগ",e: "My punishment", b: "আযাবের", i: "azab-Ku", f: 14, rm: "chastisement, castigate, punishment, torture, torment, retribution, abstain/desist (e.g. from eating due to excessive thirst), relinquish, quit. To deny a thing, hinder anyone from, be inaccessible, prevent."},
"38:9:1" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 1, r: "", t: "أَمْ", l: "أَم", lc: 124, tl: "am", lb: "অথবা",e: "Or", b: "অথবা", i: "ataukah/apakah", f: 103, rm: ""},
"38:9:2" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 2, r: "عند", t: "عِندَهُمْ", l: "عِند", lc: 197, tl: "ʿindahum", lb: "নিকটে",e: "have they", b: "তাদের কাছে", i: "disisi mereka/mereka mempunyai", f: 3, rm: "to go out of the right way, decline, deviate, be rebellious, tyrant, opposing, obstinate to resist, transgress the bounds."},
"38:9:3" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 3, r: "خزن", t: "خَزَآئِنُ", l: "خَزَآئِن", lc: 8, tl: "khazāinu", lb: "ভাণ্ডারসমূহ",e: "(the) treasures", b: "ধনভান্ডার", i: "perbendaharaan", f: 5, rm: "Reposit/store/preserve/guard something in a thing or property, conceal or withhold a thing from someone, become rich/suffcient after poverty, take the nearest of a thing."},
"38:9:4" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 4, r: "رحم", t: "رَحْمَةِ", l: "رَحْمَة", lc: 114, tl: "raḥmati", lb: "করুণা",e: "(of the) Mercy", b: "(আল্লাহর) রহমতের", i: "rahmat", f: 5, rm: ""},
"38:9:5" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 5, r: "ربب", t: "رَبِّكَ", l: "رَبّ", lc: 975, tl: "rabbika", lb: "প্রভু, সযত্নে পালনকর্তা",e: "(of) your Lord", b: "তোমার প্রভুর", i: "Tuhanmu", f: 81, rm: "to be a lord and master, collect, possess/owner, rule, increase, complete, bring up, preserve, chief, guardian, regulator, determiner, caretaker, provider, sustainer, perfecter, rewarder, creator, maintainer, reposer of properties, developer, former of rules and laws of the growth, foster a thing in such a manner as to make it attain one condition after another until it reaches its goal of completion, the bringing a thing to a state of completion by degrees, whoever possesses a thing is its rabb."},
"38:9:6" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 6, r: "عزز", t: "ٱلْعَزِيزِ", l: "عَزِيز", lc: 101, tl: "l-ʿazīzi", lb: "ক্ষমতা এবং কর্তৃত্বের অধিকারী",e: "the All-Mighty", b: "পরিপূর্ণ ক্ষমতার মালিক", i: "Maha Perkasa", f: 18, rm: "mighty/potent/powerful/strong, noble/honourable/glorious, resisted/withstood, invincible, overcome (e.g. in argument), exalt, prevail, highly esteemed, precious, glory, vanity, excellent, proud and hard manner, stern."},
"38:9:7" : {s: 38, a: 9, w: 7, r: "وهب", t: "ٱلْوَهَّابِ", l: "وَهَّاب", lc: 3, tl: "l-wahābi", lb: "অধিক দানকারী",e: "the Bestower", b: "মহাদাতা", i: "Maha Pemberi", f: 1, rm: "to give/grant/bestow, dedicate, offer as a present/gift."},
